<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n25116f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n25" href="#n25116f">N25 (VI.B.15)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n25all.htm#n25116f"> 116(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> as well the stranger</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Leviticus xxiv. 16, &lsquo;He that blasphemest the name of the Lord, he shall surely be put to death, and all the congregation shall certainly stone him: <mark>as well the stranger</mark>, as he that is born in the land, when he blasphemest the name of the Lord, shall be put to death,&rsquo; is sometimes cited as the warrant for the avoidance of the &lsquo;holy and reverend&rsquo; name Yahweh, or Jehovah <small> Edward Clodd, <a name="ECTTT" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#ECTTT"><cite title="source">Tom Tit Tot</cite></a> (1898) 189-190</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c14071g" href="c14all.htm#c14071g">VI.C.14:071(g)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
